Citation.sAbstract: The (vapour + liquid) equilibrium (VLE) and boiling temperature measurements have been determined at  95.3 kPa as a function of composition for the binary liquid mixtures of N-methyl-2-pyrrolidone (NMP)  with branched alcohols using a Swietoslawski-ebulliometer. The branched alcohols include 2-propanol,  2-butanol, 2-methyl-l- propanol, 2-methyl-2-propanol, and 3-methyl-l-butanol. The experimental temperature-  composition (T x) results were used to estimate Wilson parameters and then used to calculate  the equilibrium vapour compositions and the excess Gibbs free energy at T = 298.15 K. The experimental  temperature-composition (T,x) results were correlated with the Wilson, the NRTL and the UNIQUAC models.  The experimental results are interpreted in terms of intermolecular interactions between constituent  molecules.
Citation.sTitle: Isobaric (vapour + liquid) equilibrium for N-methyl-2-pyrrolidone with branched alcohols
sKeyword: N-methyl-2-pyrrolidone  Branched alkanols  (Vapour + liquid) equilibrium  Molecular interactions  Empirical equations
